\f2\b\fs48 \cf4 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
1. System Workflow (End-to-End)
\fs36 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f3\b0\fs24 \cf0 The application follows a 
\f2\b "Record-Process-Display"
\f3\b0  asynchronous architecture.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf5 \cb6 Phase A: The Client-Side Capture (Frontend)
\fs28 \cf0 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Initialisation :
\f3\b0  User grants microphone permissions; the system initialises a 
\f4\fs26 MediaRecorder
\f3\fs24  instance.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Active Listening :
\f3\b0  The app records audio in a high-quality format (e.g., 
\f4\fs26 .wav
\f3\fs24  or 
\f4\fs26 .m4a
\f3\fs24  at 44.1kHz).\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Metadata Tagging :
\f3\b0  The user selects a "Scenario" (e.g., 
\f5\i Interview
\f3\i0 , 
\f5\i Seminar
\f3\i0 ) which sets the benchmark parameters for the backend.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Payload Delivery :
\f3\b0  Upon clicking "Stop," the audio blob is packaged with a unique 
\f4\fs26 SessionID
\f3\fs24  and sent to the backend via a POST request.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf5 \cb6 Phase B: The Processing Pipeline (Backend)
\fs28 \cf0 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Audio Pre-processing:
\f3\b0  The system normalises volume and reduces background noise using a library like 
\f5\i Librosa
\f3\i0  or 
\f5\i FFmpeg
\f3\i0 .\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
STT Transcription (The Core):
\f3\b0  The audio is passed to a Speech-to-Text engine (e.g., OpenAI Whisper). We must request 
\f2\b timestamped JSON output
\f3\b0  (word-level timestamps).\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Algorithmic Analysis:
\f3\b0  * 
\f2\b Word Tally:
\f3\b0  Counts total tokens in the transcript.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f6 \uc0\u9702 
\f2 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Time Calculation:
\f3\b0  Subtracts the 
\f4\fs26 start_time
\f3\fs24  of the first word from the 
\f4\fs26 end_time
\f3\fs24  of the last word.\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f6 \uc0\u9702 
\f2 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Gap Analysis:
\f3\b0  Measures the duration between the 
\f4\fs26 end_time
\f3\fs24  of 
\f4\fs26 Word[n]
\f3\fs24  and the 
\f4\fs26 start_time
\f3\fs24  of 
\f4\fs26 Word[n+1]
\f3\fs24 .\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
LLM Layer:
\f3\b0  The raw stats and transcript are sent to an LLM (e.g., GPT-4o-mini) to generate a human-readable summary and "Clarity" qualitative feedback.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf5 \cb6 Phase C: Reporting (Frontend)
\fs28 \cf0 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The backend returns a JSON object. The frontend parses this to render charts (Speed over time) and the final summary.\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs48 \cf4 2. Outcomes of the Processed Text
\fs36 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f3\b0\fs24 \cf0 The backend must output a structured data object. Here is the required schema for the "Outcomes" report:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf5 \cb6 A. Quantitative Metrics (Hard Data)
\fs28 \cf0 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Total Word Count:
\f3\b0  Integer count of all transcribed words.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Gross WPM:
\f3\b0  (Total Words / Total Recording Time) \'d7 60.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Net WPM (Fluidity):
\f3\b0  (Total Words / (Total Recording Time - Long Pauses)) \'d7 60.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Filler Frequency:
\f3\b0  A dictionary of detected crutch words and their counts:\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl1
\f4\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f7 \uc0\u9702 
\f4 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\{"um": 4, "uh": 2, "like": 7, "actually": 1\}
\f3\fs24 .\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Pause Map:
\f3\b0  A list of timestamps where silence exceeded 2.0 seconds.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf5 \cb6 B. Qualitative Insights (AI-Derived)
\fs28 \cf0 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Clarity Score (0-100%):
\f3\b0  Based on the STT engine's confidence score for each word. Low confidence usually indicates mumbling or mispronunciation.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Pace Evaluation:
\f3\b0  A categorical result based on the chosen scenario:\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl1
\f5\i \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f8 \uc0\u9702 
\f5 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Example:
\f3\i0  If Scenario = "Seminar" and WPM > 160, Result = "Too Fast".\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Sentiment & Tone:
\f3\b0  Analysis of the user's vocal energy (e.g., "Confident," "Anxious," or "Monotone").\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf5 \cb6 C. The "Actionable Summary"
\fs28 \cf0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f3\b0\fs24 \cf0 The final text output provided to the user should follow this logic:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The "Good":
\f3\b0  Positive reinforcement (e.g., "Great vocabulary variety").\
\ls6\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The "Bad":
\f3\b0  Highlight the primary friction point (e.g., "Your speed increased significantly in the last 30 seconds").\
\ls6\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The "How-To":
\f3\b0  One specific instruction for the next practice session (e.g., "Try to pause for 1 second after each sentence to lower your WPM").\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

